item.title: CVE-2020-1696|2024-08-04T06:46:30.878Z -- %5Bunknown%5D -- pki-core
item.description: A flaw was found in the all pki-core 10.x.x versions, where Token Processing Service (TPS) where it did not properly sanitize Profile IDs, enabling a Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability when the profile ID is printed. An attacker with sufficient permissions could trick an authenticated victim into executing a specially crafted Javascript code.
